## 📊 Air Pollutants & Greenhouse Gas Emissions Over Time 🌍

Thrilled to present my recent environmental data analysis project! This study focuses on understanding the trends of air pollutants and greenhouse gas emissions over time and their impact on the environment and human health 👇

🔍 **What I Did:**
• Collected and analyzed emission data across different years  
• Performed Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to identify patterns and trends  
• Compared various pollutants and greenhouse gases  
• Studied relationships between emissions, industrial growth, and urbanization  

📈 **Key Insights:**
• Significant increase in emissions due to industrialization & fossil fuel consumption  
• Carbon dioxide (CO₂) remains the major contributor to global warming  
• Urban areas show higher pollution levels compared to rural regions  
• Rising emissions are strongly linked to climate change and extreme weather events  

🤖 **Approach Used:**
• Data Analysis & Visualization  
• Trend Analysis  
• Comparative Study  

🛠 **Tech Stack:**
• Python  
• Pandas & NumPy  
• Matplotlib / Seaborn  

📁 **Project Workflow:**
• Data Collection  
